TextSection.Contents: A rare genetic multisystemic neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by a distinct facial appearance cardiac anomalies (most frequently supravalvular aortic stenosis) cognitive and developmental abnormalities and connective tissue abnormalities (e.g. joint laxity). Facial dysmorphism is characterized by a broad forehead bitemporal narrowing periorbital fullness stellate and/or lacy iris pattern short upturned nose with bulbous tip long philtrum wide mouth full lips and mild micrognathia.
